# LemonCrow License

LemonCrow is open-core: an open-source runtime plus a proprietary engine.

Copyright 2026 Pankaj Kumar (d/b/a LemonCrow)

## Open source — Apache-2.0

All source code published in this repository is licensed under the Apache
License, Version 2.0. See `LICENSE-APACHE` for the full text.

## Proprietary engine (required at runtime)

The LemonCrow **engine** — the `lemoncrow.pro` package (the retrieval-quality
and token-savings core, the product's moat) — is **proprietary** and is NOT
licensed under Apache-2.0.

- It is distributed **only as compiled binaries** (`.so`); its source is not
  published.
- Where its source is present in this repository (`src/lemoncrow/pro/`), that
  source is proprietary and is not licensed for use, copying, modification, or
  redistribution.
- The engine is **required for the software to function.** The open-source
  runtime loads it at runtime; without the compiled engine, LemonCrow falls
  back to a degraded built-in-only mode.

## Backend services

`services/` (the auth/payments backend) is proprietary and licensed separately
under its own `LICENSE` file. It is never published.

